154
00:07:31,960 --> 00:07:38,280
So if you go all out when you're making breakfast, it means you just, you cooked a lot or really
所以如果你做早餐时全力以赴，意味着你做了很多或做得

155
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:41,080
good and you spend a lot of time doing it.
非常好，花了很多时间。

156
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:45,640
Or for example, if it's someone's birthday and I know it's their birthday, I go all out
或者例如，如果是某人的生日，我知道是他们的生日，我会全力以赴

157
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:51,240
by buying gifts and a cake and lots of decorations and calling all of their friends and having
买礼物、蛋糕和很多装饰，叫上所有朋友，举办

158
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,240
a party.
派对。

159
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:54,600
So this is doing everything for them.
所以这是为他们做一切。

160
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:55,600
That's right.
没错。

161
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,600
Okay.
好的。

162
00:07:56,600 --> 00:08:01,800
And he was really surprised and he really seemed to enjoy breakfast and he said, looks
他真的很惊讶，而且看起来非常享受早餐，他说，

163
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,800
good.
看起来不错。

164
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:08,080
Okay, this is a way to say good job or nicely done.
好的，这是一种说“做得好”或“干得漂亮”的方式。

165
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:11,440
It's almost a way to say, I'm happy about this.
这几乎是在说“我对这个很满意”。

166
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:16,560
Or yeah, and obviously you can also say that the food looks delicious, so it looks good.
或者，当然你也可以说食物看起来很好吃，所以“看起来不错”。

167
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,560
It looks good.
看起来不错。

168
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:23,400
So it's a way to say, you know, well done, looks good or in this case, looks very tasty.
所以这是一种表达“干得好，看起来不错”的方式，或者在这里是“看起来很好吃”。

169
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:24,400
That's right.
没错。

170
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:25,400
Okay.
好的。

171
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,440
And now this is an interesting part.
现在这是一个有趣的部分。

172
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:30,360
He says, I'll squeeze us some fresh orange juice.
他说，我来给我们榨点新鲜橙汁。

173
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:33,320
So let's take a look at this verb, squeeze.
那我们来看看这个动词，“榨”。

174
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:34,660
To squeeze.
榨。

175
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:39,220
This is something you usually do with your hand when you tighten something.
这通常是你用手拧紧某物时做的动作。

176
00:08:39,220 --> 00:08:41,480
So for example, your toothpaste.
比如，你的牙膏。

177
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:45,200
Yes, you squeeze your toothpaste so the toothpaste will come out.
是的，你挤牙膏，这样牙膏就会出来。

178
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:50,120
So in this case, we are squeezing the orange juice to extract the juice.
所以在这里，我们是在榨橙汁来提取果汁。

179
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,120
That's right.
没错。

180
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:55,560
So you, you hold the orange very tight, you make the juice come out and then you have
所以你紧紧握住橙子，让果汁流出来，然后你就得到了

181
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:58,080
fresh squeezed orange juice.
鲜榨橙汁。

182
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:00,840
And this is different from orange juice you buy in a store.
这和你在商店买的橙汁不同。

183
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,840
Okay.
好的。

184
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:05,400
So you can say, I'll squeeze us some fresh orange juice.
所以你可以说，我来给我们榨点新鲜橙汁。

185
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:08,640
That means you're going to make fresh orange juice.
这意味着你要做新鲜橙汁。

186
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:13,640
And this fresh orange juice that you make is called fresh squeezed orange juice.
而你做的这种新鲜橙汁叫做鲜榨橙汁。

187
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,760
Fresh squeezed.
鲜榨的。

188
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:19,680
You've probably seen this in the store, like some bottles, they say a hundred percent fresh
你可能在商店里见过，比如有些瓶子上写着“100%鲜榨橙汁”之类的。

189
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:21,000
squeezed orange juice or something.
鲜榨橙汁之类的。

190
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,560
Yeah, it's good for advertising.
是啊，这对广告有好处。

191
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:23,880
All right.
好了。

192
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:24,880
So very good.
所以非常好。

193
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,760
A lot of great, interesting phrases there.
这里有很多很棒、有趣的短语。

194
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:30,360
Why don't we listen to our dialogue one last time?
我们最后再听一遍对话好吗？

195
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:36,480
Smells good.
闻起来真香。

196
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,480
What's for breakfast?
早餐吃什么？

197
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:41,880
Well, since we're getting up so late, I decided to make a big breakfast.
嗯，既然我们起得这么晚，我决定做一顿丰盛的早餐。

198
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:43,360
Nice brunch.
不错的早午餐。

199
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:44,920
Kind of.
差不多吧。

200
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:50,680
So I made scrambled and soft boiled eggs, some French toast and buttermilk pancakes.
所以我做了炒蛋和溏心蛋，一些法式吐司和酪乳煎饼。

201
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:51,680
Wow.
哇。

202
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:52,880
You really went all out.
你真是全力以赴了。

203
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:54,120
Did you make any coffee?
你煮咖啡了吗？

204
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,220
Yeah, just the way you like it.
煮了，就按你喜欢的口味。

205
00:09:56,220 --> 00:10:00,680
I also put out some cereal and muesli if you feel like having something more light.
我还放了一些麦片和什锦麦片，如果你想吃得清淡点的话。

206
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:01,680
Looks good.
看起来不错。

207
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,880
I'll squeeze us some fresh orange juice.
我来给我们榨点新鲜橙汁。

208
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:05,880
Get the jam and butter while you are in there.
你在那里的时候把果酱和黄油拿来。

209
00:10:05,880 --> 00:10:08,200
Oh, and don't forget the syrup.
哦，别忘了糖浆。

210
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,200
All righty.
好的。

211
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:12,160
All right.
好了。

212
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:17,640
So talking about brunch and breakfast, what is your typical or ideal breakfast?
说到早午餐和早餐，你典型或理想的早餐是什么？

213
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:18,800
That's a hard question.
这是个很难的问题。

214
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,720
Breakfast is my favorite meal of the day.
早餐是我一天中最喜欢的一餐。

215
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:24,320
So I could eat breakfast, all kinds of breakfast anytime.
所以我随时都能吃早餐，各种早餐都行。

216
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:28,640
But one of my favorite kinds of breakfast is a Greek diner breakfast.
但我最喜欢的早餐之一是希腊式小餐馆早餐。

217
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:29,640
Greek diner.
希腊式小餐馆。

218
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:30,640
What does this have?
这有什么？

219
00:10:30,640 --> 00:10:37,400
Well, we have a lot of diners or small restaurants that are very, very cheap and fast in America.
嗯，美国有很多非常便宜又快捷的小餐馆或小餐厅。

220
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:45,880
And this usually involves some scrambled eggs that are made with cheese and toast and potatoes
这通常包括用奶酪做的炒蛋、吐司、土豆、

221
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:48,960
and bacon and sausage and a coffee.
培根、香肠和一杯咖啡。

222
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:49,960
Wow.
哇。

223
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:50,960
Big breakfast.
丰盛的早餐。

224
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:51,960
Very big.
非常丰盛。

225
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,960
But delicious.
但很好吃。

226
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:53,960
Nice.
不错。

227
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:54,960
What's your favorite?
你最喜欢什么？

228
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,520
I also really, really like breakfast.
我也非常非常喜欢早餐。

229
00:10:56,520 --> 00:11:01,440
And I actually like having places that you can have 24-hour a day breakfast.
而且我其实喜欢那些能24小时提供早餐的地方。

230
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,680
All day breakfast is called.
这叫做全天早餐。

231
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:04,080
So I can have breakfast for dinner.
所以我可以晚餐吃早餐。

232
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,080
Right.
对。

233
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:08,480
That's usually in America, you go to a diner because they have breakfast at four o'clock
在美国，你通常会去小餐馆，因为他们凌晨四点或晚上七点都有早餐。

234
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:11,160
in the morning or at seven o'clock at night.
凌晨四点或晚上七点。

235
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:13,320
I'm not really a coffee person.
我不是一个爱喝咖啡的人。

236
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:17,560
I actually enjoy either juice, orange juice, or hot chocolate.
我其实喜欢果汁、橙汁或热巧克力。

237
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,400
I really like hot chocolate.
我真的很喜欢热巧克力。

238
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,800
And definitely pancakes.
而且绝对要有煎饼。

239
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:23,240
Three buttermilk pancakes stacked.
三个酪乳煎饼叠在一起。

240
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:26,120
And as you said before, syrup.
就像你之前说的，糖浆。

241
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,120
But I actually also put butter on it.
但我其实还在上面抹了黄油。

242
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:29,120
Gross.
真恶心。

243
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,120
I know a lot of people who do that.
我知道很多人会这么做。

244
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,880
They put butter on first and then they pour the syrup.
他们先抹黄油，然后再倒糖浆。

245
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:34,360
Yeah, of course.
是啊，当然。

246
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:37,160
So it's like complete, very, very fatty.
所以这简直是一份完整、非常非常油腻的早餐。

247
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:38,160
And hash browns.
还有土豆煎饼。

248
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:40,360
I'm definitely a fan of hash browns.
我绝对是土豆煎饼的粉丝。

249
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:44,840
Those are potatoes that are chopped very, very finely and you fry them together.
那些是把土豆切得非常非常细，然后一起煎炸的东西。

250
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:48,120
So it almost becomes like a potato pancake.
所以它几乎变成了像土豆饼一样的东西。

251
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,760
Yeah, exactly.
对，没错。

252
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:50,960
So a lot of great stuff.
所以有很多好东西。

253
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:53,680
And obviously, breakfasts around the world are different.
显然，世界各地的早餐都不一样。

254
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:57,360
I know, for example, in some countries, they have the fisherman's breakfast.
我知道，比如在一些国家，他们有渔夫早餐。

255
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:00,960
So in the morning, you have black coffee, rice, and fish.
所以早上，你会喝黑咖啡、吃米饭和鱼。

256
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,960
That's right.
没错。

257
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,000
Because you're going to work all day.
因为你要工作一整天。

258
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:06,080
So we're really curious about how breakfast is in your country.
所以我们很好奇你们国家的早餐是什么样的。

259
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,560
What a typical breakfast is like.
典型的早餐是什么样的。

260
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:10,960
Yeah, what are traditional breakfasts and what is your favorite breakfast?
是啊，传统的早餐是什么，你最喜欢的早餐又是什么？

261
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,400
Let us know on our website, EnglishPod.com.
在我们的网站 EnglishPod.com 上告诉我们吧。

262
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:14,400
We hope to see you there.
我们期待在那里见到你。

263
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,400
All right.
好的。

264
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,400
Bye.
再见。

265
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:28,440
I mean, we have good up-to-date advertising.
我是说，我们有最新的广告。
